result.execSummary:
The defendant Corey L Buckholtz was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Failure to Support Child (120 Days+), a class I felony, Wisconsin Statutes 948.22(2).
  • Failure to Support Child (120 Days+), a class I felony, Wisconsin Statutes 948.22(2).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

supervisions.notes:
The defendant shall pay Department of Correction fees as directed by the agent.
Concurrent with: Probation on counts 1&2 to run concurrent to each other.

miscConds.notes: Costs to be paid on a schedule established by the agent. Defendant is ordered to pay the $250.00 DNA surcharge on each count, provide a sample for testing through the Dept. of Corrections as required in felony convictions.

Defendant is to remain employed and not change employment without agents approval, if not employed,face to face job search of 10 job applications per week, if employed  only part time, face to face job search of 5 job applications per week  and report these to his agent.

Defendant shall not possess or consume any alcohol, and not go into places that sell alcohol except incidentally such as a grocery store, convenience store or gas station or other such place where alcohol is not sold for consumption on the premises. EXCEPTION: Defendant may work in a place where alcohol is sold , but is on the premises only during scheduled working hours and is to remain alcohol free.  

The defendant shall submit to random urine/PBT testing as required by the agent or any law enforcement agent without cause.

Defendant is specifically prohibited from leaving the State of Wisconsin at any time for any reason or any length of time.   AMENDED 05/01/2015  The defendant cannot leave the State of Wisconsin without prior approval of his agent, not to exceed two (2) weeks at a time or eight (8) weeks in any one year.

Defendant is to comply with all current and future Child Support orders. Defendant is to meet all payment obligations and is to turn over each years(State & Federal) tax returns within 24 hours of said returns being filed with the government. Defendant is to report any change of address to both the Child Support Agent and DOC Agent prior to any move and then only moving with the agents approval.

timeConds.notes:
Defendant is denied huber for the first 60 days of conditional jail sentence but may have huber priveleges for the last 60 days of sentence. Defendant is specifically denied any credit for time served at this point, instead credit will be applied when and if probation is revoked.
Jail sentence applies to count 1 only.

supervisions.notes:
Defendant was granted 420 days credit for time served.
Concurrent with: Prison term on Ct 2 in this case

superMiscConds.notes: The defendant is to submit to an Alcohol and Other Drug Assessment (AODA) and follow the recommendations, releasing the findings to the agent.

Defendant is ordered to pay the DNA surcharge, and to make arrangements to provide a DNA sample, within 48 hours, for testing through the Clark County Sheriff Department or if on probation, to the Department of Corrections as is required in all criminal convictions.  Fine and/or costs to be paid on a schedule established by the agent.
The defendant shall pay Department of Correction fees as directed by the agent.  The defendant shall submit to random urine/PBT testing as required by the agent or any law enforcement officer.
Defendant shall attend counseling, treatments, programming, evaluations as deemed appropriate by the agent releasing all records to the agent upon request

Defendant shall not possess or consume any alcohol, and not go into places that sell alcohol except incidentally such as a grocery store, convenience store or gas station or other such place where alcohol is not sold for consumption on the premises.
Defendant is to remain employed and not change employment without agents approval, if not employed job search of 10 job applications per week and report then to his agent.

Defendant is to comply with all current and future Child Support orders. Defendant is to meet all payment obligations and is to turn over each years(State & Federal) tax returns within 24 hours of said returns being filed with the government to both his agent and to the Child Support Agency
